# Liabilities Other Financial Liabilities Borrowings Loan Capital Hybrid Securities Amount

## identifier
de8306

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of borrowings, loan capital and hybrid securities as determined in accordance with accounting standards.

Borrowings are generally amounts of money on loan from financial institutions or other creditors with the promise or understanding that it will be repaid.

For the purposes of this item, include hybrid securities classified as debt securities, loan capital, and certificates of deposit.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Liabilities.OtherFinancialLiabilities.BorrowingsLoanCapitalHybridSecurities.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo6.02.06
- period=instant
